16/9 yet to add:
In the home-school parent, there needs to be the capacity for lesson planning and scope and sequence to enable at-home learning for their children as students. Parents need to show curriculum alignment.
Home-school Parents take full responsibility for planning and delivering their child’s education, selecting and adapting the curriculum, and teaching materials, and setting the learning schedule. Homeschooling is typically registered and regulated by the state’s education authority.
Educational Plan: Parents are required to provide an outline of the educational program they intend to deliver. This plan should demonstrate how the curriculum will cover key learning areas and meet the educational standards of the state.
I would like the companion aspect to be inherently integrated into the system and to primarily inform chatbot outputs so that when educators (parents and teachers) get a leeson plan or scope and sequence or lesson resources, etc. developed they are created within the guidelines of Montessori and that they also include any Australian Curriculum V.9 content descriptor codes or Achievement standard reference. This way, educators can show proof to auditors that there is alignment to the Montessori Curriculum and the Australian Curriculum. While Montessori has an extensive primary school and early years reference, it is imperative that adolescent learning plays an equally prominent role in this app. However, I do like the option for all users to explore the companion sections you've created, but it is secondary to the intention of the app, which is to create a Montessori-guided education planning tool for parents and teachers and a tutor-like experience for students.
Revert back to Teachers and Parents requiring a login with email and password, and the capacity to create a username and password login for their students. 